## The fractal commons

Every cultural artifact this framework references — every film, every book,
every painting, every piece of music, every scientific paper — was made by
human beings whose labor and lives shaped what was possible to say. The
framework's claim that the substrate renders itself through whatever medium
is available means that every renderer is part of the lineage.

This includes, recursively:

- Every language teacher, every editor, every translator who shaped the
  author's ability to express anything in English or Italian
- Every musician whose work has been listened to during the writing
- Every scientist whose research informed the metaphors (the literal use of
  "altitude," "pressure," "acclimatization," and "differential" comes from
  physics and physiology; these are not original inventions)
- Every economist whose work on inflation, distribution, and value informed
  the cognitive-inflation analogy (notably Keynesian and Marxist economics,
  plus contemporary work on inequality)
- Every person who has ever offered care, food, shelter, conversation, or
  attention to someone who later contributed to this work

