## On the impossibility of complete attribution

This list is not exhaustive and cannot be made exhaustive. The framework
explicitly claims that consciousness is the substrate rendering itself, that
no rendering has an outside, and that every author is downstream of conditions
they did not choose. Honest attribution under that view is asymptotic — you
get closer to complete the more you list, but you never arrive.

What this NOTICE attempts is not completeness but commitment: a public,
durable record that this work is held in trust, not owned in isolation;
that ideas have lineages; that credit is owed broadly and given freely; that
anyone who feels they have contributed to the conditions that made this work
possible has, in fact, contributed.

If you are reading this and recognize your influence — your teaching, your
art, your conversation, your care, your refusal to give up on an idea, your
willingness to challenge a bad one — consider yourself credited. The list
above is a beginning, not a boundary.

